  "bib_entries": {
    "27065173": {
      "title": "Modeling interstitial flow in an artery wall allows estimation of wall shear stress on smooth muscle cells",
      "abstract": "The arterial media is modeled as a periodic array of cylindrical smooth muscle cells residing in a matrix comprised of proteoglycan and collagen fibers. Using Brinkman's model to describe transmural flow through such a fibrous media, we calculate the effective hydraulic permeability of the media and the wall shear stress on smooth muscle cells. Two interesting results are obtained : first, the wall shear stress on smooth muscle cells is on the order of 1 dyne/cm 2 , which is in the range known to affect endothelial cells in vitro ; second, the flow resistance due to smooth muscle cells is not negligible compared to the resistance due to the fiber matrix."
    }
  },
